Like children all over the country the children of Whitminster play a wide variety of games. Many of the games they play have not changed for generations and are well remembered by their parents as well. Here are a few examples.
{The Clapping Game.}
For the Clapping Game you start with your hands in special position. One up in the air and one down below. You need a partner to clap with. First you clap together twice and then on your own. You clap to a song which goes like this: "A sailor went to sea, sea, sea To see what he could see, see, see And all that he could see, see, see Was the bottom of the deep blue sea, sea, sea". Continued on page 11.
